<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>News & Media | Navigator +</title>
    <%- include('partials/styles.ejs') %>
    <style>
        body { padding-top: 86px; }
        .news-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius-panel); padding: 26px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(15,42,30,0.07); margin-bottom: 22px; }
        .news-date { font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-muted); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; font-family: var(--font-display); }

        .news-tabs { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
        .news-tab-btn {
            border: 2px solid var(--brand-red);
            background: transparent;
            color: var(--brand-red);
            font-weight: 600;
            padding: 10px 28px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        .news-tab-btn.active { background: var(--brand-red); color: #fff; }
        .news-tab-panel { display: none; }
        .news-tab-panel.active { display: block; }

        .news-card.intl { border-left: 4px solid var(--brand-red); }
        .news-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            font-size: 11px;
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: 0.03em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: #8a5060;
            background: #fbeef1;
            border-radius: 999px;
            padding: 3px 12px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs', { page: 'news' }) %>

    <div class="page-hero text-center">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="display-6">News & Media</h1>
            <p class="mx-auto">The latest road safety campaigns, enforcement changes and community initiatives.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mt-4 mb-5">

        <div class="news-tabs" role="tablist">
            <button type="button" class="news-tab-btn active" id="tab-local-btn" onclick="showNewsTab('local')" role="tab" aria-selected="true">🇸🇬 Local</button>
            <button type="button" class="news-tab-btn" id="tab-intl-btn" onclick="showNewsTab('intl')" role="tab" aria-selected="false">🌐 International</button>
        </div>

        <div class="news-tab-panel active" id="tab-local">

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">07 July 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.channelnewsasia.com/singapore/dangerous-driving-jail-drink-alcohol-limit-drugs-parliament-6224456" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stricter penalties and a lower drink-driving limit on the way</a></h5>
            <p>In response to a rising fatality rate, authorities announced plans to lower Singapore's legal blood-alcohol limit to bring it closer to other Asian jurisdictions, alongside a review of sentencing for dangerous driving. Officials pointed to Helsinki's "Vision Zero" approach — zero road deaths over a 12-month period — as proof that a much safer road culture is achievable.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: CNA</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">30 May 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.police.gov.sg/media-hub/news/2026/05/20260530_singapore_road_safety_month_2026_community_road_safety_day_at_our_tampines_hub" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Singapore Road Safety Month 2026: "Road Safety Begins with Us"</a></h5>
            <p>Traffic Police and the Singapore Road Safety Council launched this year's month-long campaign at Our Tampines Hub, focusing on the outsized risks faced by elderly pedestrians and motorcyclists. New neighbourhood outreach will bring storytelling sessions for preschoolers and safe-route walks for seniors, delivered through all 32 Neighbourhood Police Centres.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: Singapore Police Force Media Hub</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">07 March 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/traffic-police-launches-new-initiative-to-urge-all-road-users-to-ensure-each-others-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New "Road Users on Watch" initiative launched after a decade-high death toll</a></h5>
            <p>Following news that 2025 traffic deaths hit a 10-year high, the Ministry of Home Affairs launched "Road Users on Watch," expanding an earlier cyclist-focused scheme to all road users. The push emphasises that safety often comes down to small everyday choices — a driver's attention, a cyclist's habits, a pedestrian's care at a crossing — rather than dramatic recklessness alone.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: The Straits Times</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">12 January 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/politics/maximum-fines-for-lorry-owners-who-flout-speed-limiter-rules-to-be-raised-by-10-times" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maximum fines for lorry owners who flout speed limiter rules may rise to 10 times current penalties</a></h5>
            <p>Under a phased mandate, lorries fitted with speed limiters have seen speeding violations fall by roughly 90% compared with unfitted vehicles. It's held up by officials as an example of how combining technology with enforcement can measurably improve road safety outcomes.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: The Straits Times</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">07 November 2025</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.police.gov.sg/Media-Hub/News/2025/11/20251107_singapore_traffic_games_2025_bringing_road_safety_education_closer_to_schools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Singapore Traffic Games 2025 – Bringing Road Safety Education Closer To Schools</a></h5>
            <p>Running since 1958, this annual inter-school event lets primary school children experience the roles of pedestrians, cyclists and go-kart drivers to build good road safety habits early. The 2025 finals drew over 200 students and teachers to the Road Safety Community Park.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: Singapore Police Force</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card">
            <div class="news-date">31 October 2025</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.channelnewsasia.com/singapore/traffic-violation-enforcement-cameras-police-illegal-u-turn-road-safety-5435016" target="_blank" rel="noopener">New traffic cameras rolling out to catch more violation types</a></h5>
            <p>Traffic Police have been trialling new Traffic Violation Enforcement Cameras that use video analytics and number-plate recognition to detect offences like illegal U-turns, crossing double white lines, and stopping in yellow boxes — going beyond what traditional speed and red-light cameras can catch. Full rollout is expected through 2026.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: CNA</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-4">
            <p>Follow ongoing coverage and official updates directly from these sources:</p>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
                <a href="https://www.srsc.org.sg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand">Singapore Road Safety Council</a>
                <a href="https://roads.sg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">ROADS.sg</a>
                <a href="https://www.mot.gov.sg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">Ministry of Transport</a>
                <a href="https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/who_we_are.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">LTA</a>
                <a href="https://www.police.gov.sg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">Singapore Police Force</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        </div><!-- /#tab-local -->

        <div class="news-tab-panel" id="tab-intl">

        <div class="news-card intl">
            <span class="news-badge">WHO</span>
            <div class="news-date">20 May 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.who.int/news/item/20-05-2026-world-must--double-down-on-delivery--for-global-road-safety--says-who" target="_blank" rel="noopener">World must "double down on delivery" for global road safety, says WHO</a></h5>
            <p>At a UN hearing in New York previewing the July 2026 High-Level Meeting on Road Safety, WHO and civil society leaders warned that nearly 1.2 million people are killed on the world's roads each year and called it a "silent pandemic." Speakers said the world doesn't lack knowledge but an implementation gap, urging stronger enforcement, safer infrastructure and child-focused measures to hit the UN's target of halving road deaths by 2030.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: World Health Organization</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card intl">
            <span class="news-badge">WHO</span>
            <div class="news-date">1 July 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.who.int/news/item/01-07-2026-who-convenes-global-experts-to-develop-new-road-safety-legal-guidance" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WHO convenes global experts to develop new road safety legal guidance</a></h5>
            <p>A new WHO Global Technical Working Group of 17 experts from all six WHO regions met for the first time to draft legal guidance on speed management, distracted driving and road infrastructure — three risk factors behind the 1.19 million road deaths recorded worldwide each year. Road crashes remain the leading killer of people aged 5 to 29.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: World Health Organization</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card intl">
            <span class="news-badge">UK Government</span>
            <div class="news-date">7 January 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/thousands-of-lives-to-be-saved-under-bold-new-road-safety-strategy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UK launches first Road Safety Strategy in over a decade</a></h5>
            <p>Britain's new strategy targets a 65% cut in road deaths and serious injuries by 2035, with a steeper 70% reduction goal for children under 16. Measures under consultation include a lower drink-drive limit, mandatory eyesight tests for drivers over 70, and a minimum learning period for new drivers — built around a "safe system" approach covering roads, road users, speeds, vehicles and post-crash response.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: GOV.UK</p>
        </div>

        <div class="news-card intl">
            <span class="news-badge">NHTSA (USA)</span>
            <div class="news-date">2 July 2026</div>
            <h5><a href="https://www.nhtsa.gov/press-releases/trumps-transportation-department-reminds-drivers-that-speeding-catches-you" target="_blank" rel="noopener">"Speeding Catches Up with You": US campaign targets a leading killer on the road</a></h5>
            <p>The US National Highway Traffic Safety Administration launched a month-long enforcement and awareness campaign after speeding-related deaths contributed to roughly 29% of all US traffic fatalities in 2024. Early estimates for the first quarter of 2026 show fatality rates falling to close to a record low, even as Americans drove billions more miles than the year before.</p>
            <p class="source-note mb-0">Source: NHTSA</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-4">
            <p>Explore international road safety data and campaigns directly from these organisations:</p>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center gap-3 flex-wrap">
                <a href="https://www.who.int/teams/social-determinants-of-health/safety-and-mobility/road-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand">World Health Organization</a>
                <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">UK Dept for Transport</a>
                <a href="https://www.nhtsa.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-brand-outline" style="color: var(--brand-red); border-color: var(--brand-red);">NHTSA (USA)</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        </div><!-- /#tab-intl -->

    </div>

    <script>
        function showNewsTab(tab) {
            document.getElementById('tab-local').classList.toggle('active', tab === 'local');
            document.getElementById('tab-intl').classList.toggle('active', tab === 'intl');
            document.getElementById('tab-local-btn').classList.toggle('active', tab === 'local');
            document.getElementById('tab-intl-btn').classList.toggle('active', tab === 'intl');
            document.getElementById('tab-local-btn').setAttribute('aria-selected', tab === 'local');
            document.getElementById('tab-intl-btn').setAttribute('aria-selected', tab === 'intl');
        }
    </script>

    <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>
